summary: Email correspondence from October 2, 2020, regarding booking travel reservations for a trip to London, explicitly stated to be for the Epstein case. The email chain involves a request for flight bookings and mentions two travelers.

events.title: Planned trip to London
events.description: A planned trip to London involving two individuals, with a departure on a redeye flight and a return on October 17, 2020. The travel is stated to be for the Epstein case.

keyFacts: The email explicitly states the travel is 'for the Epstein case'.
Travel was being arranged for two individuals to fly to London on October 12, 2020, returning October 17, 2020.
The correspondence indicates ongoing activity or investigation related to the Epstein case in October 2020.
The email chain shows coordination for booking refundable fares on U.S. carriers for the trip.
